ZCZC OE54
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 112300 UTC
LOW PRESSURE 1000 IS EXP TO BE JUST NW OF SCOTLAND INITIALLY AND WILL
TRACK EWARDS INTO THE NERN N SEA BY EARLY SATURDAY WHILE SLWY FLN. THIS LOW
THEN MERGES WITH ANOTHER LOW ACROSS SCANDINAVIA TO LEAVE A TROUGH EXTENDING
W TOWARDS FAEROES AND SW ACROSS MUCH OF THE N SEA THROUGH THE REST OF SATURDAY.
MEANWHILE A SECOND LOW 1003 W OF FITZROY TRACKS N AND EXTENDS A TROUGH TOWARDS
IRELAND ALSO DPN FOR A TIME. A SLACKER PRESSURE PATTERN DOMINATES ACROSS
NWERN PORTPATRICK AS A WEAK RIDGE BUILDS N TOWARDS ICELAND. HIGH PRESSURE
LOOKS LIKELY PERSIST ACROSS ICELAND AND FAEROES THROUGH SUNDAY WHILE THE
LOW W OF IRELAND TRACKS E ACROSS THE UK ON SUNDAY AND INTO THE N SEA ON MONDAY.
THE RIDGE TOPPLES E ON MONDAY AS LOW PRESSURE DEVELOPS ACROSS OR TO THE N
OF ICELAND. NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS MAY DEVELOP ON THE SERN FLANK OF THE LOW
ON FRIDAY NIGHT
